                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/34<hi rend="superscript">2/12</hi>:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-29T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 29, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>54. From the Under Secretary. Your 58, May 25, 1 p.m. Captain B. L. Canaga, U. S.
                    Navy, and Lieutenant Colonel A. R. Harris, U. S. Army, have been designated by
                    their respective Departments to undertake the proposed conversations in Lima
                    with the Peruvian authorities. They will travel on special passports and carry
                    credentials as diplomatic couriers.</p>
                <p>They are proceeding direct by Panagra plane to Santiago and following the
                    termination of their conversations there will proceed to Lima and Quito. You
                    will be advised in advance through the Embassy in Santiago of their exact date
                    of arrival in Lima. [Welles.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
